T1  - Anxiety and depression in polycystic ovary syndrome: a comprehensive investigation.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.fertnstert.2009.09.018
A1  - Deeks, Amanda A
A1  - Gibson-Helm, Melanie E
A1  - Teede, Helena J
Y1  - 2010//
Y2  - 20100201//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is associated with high levels of depression, which impact quality of life and limit self-efficacy, yet less is known about prevalence of anxiety. This cross-sectional, observational study of community-based women with PCOS comprehensively examined mood and found that anxiety existed at higher levels than depression, anxiety was underdiagnosed, and more women with PCOS who reported infertility were depressed. Copyright 2010 American Society for Reproductive Medicine. Published by Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
