DB  - Ovid MEDLINE(R) <2005 to 2007>
ID  - 16798286
T1  - Prenatal growth restraint followed by catch-up of weight: a hyperinsulinemic pathway to polycystic ovary syndrome.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.fertnstert.2006.03.013
A1  - de Zegher, Francis
A1  - Ibanez, Lourdes
Y1  - 2006//
N2  - One of the pathways to polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) starts with an early-life sequence of prenatal growth restraint followed by catch-up of weight during infancy. This sequence results by mid-childhood in a pre-PCOS state including hyperinsulinemia, a low-grade proinflammatory state, an amplified adrenarche (with or without precocious pubarche), and an adipose body composition even in the absence of obesity. This variant of pre-PCOS and PCOS responds well to intervention with metformin.
